                <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Sabinus <expan><abbr>aed</abbr><ex>ilis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Sol</abbr><ex>vensium</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ivus</ex></expan>? <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ecit</ex></expan>? sibi<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> et<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied>niae Amabili uxori <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>niae Verae nepti <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>norum</ex></expan> VI
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Zwei Fragmente vom Architrav wohl eines Aedicula-Grabs; auf der Unterseite Soffitte mit Rankenmotiv. Inschriftfeld in Form einer tabula ansata; Fragment b (ohne Inschrift; mit der rechten ansa) ist verschollen.</p>
